<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-231-232 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 409 300</DOCID><JOURNAL>The LocalNetter  Feb 1991 v11 n2 p24(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Architecture Technology Corp. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft ships LAN Manager multiprocessor enhancements.andO;(Microsoft LAN Manager Multiprocessor Server Pak)(local areanetworks) (New Products) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   LAN Manager (Network management software) (Product enhancement)LAN Manager Multiprocessor Server Pak (Add-in/on software)(Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionEnhancementsNetwork Management SoftwareAdd-In/On Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Microsoft Ships LAN Manager Multiprocessor Enhancements Microsoft Corporationannounced the immediate availability of multiprocessor enhancements toMicrosoft LAN Manager.andP;  The first implementation runs on a dual-processorCOMPAQ SYSTEMPRO.andM;The new Microsoft LAN Manager Multiprocessor Server Pak is available throughMicrosoft's channel of authorized network specialists as an add-on tostandard LAN Manager.andP;  The multiprocessor pack makes use of a secondmicroprocessor--either an Intel 80386 or 80486--by apportioning tasks betweenthe two processors.andM;Microsoft's multiprocessor enhancements are designed to be implemented on avariety of PC-based hardware systems, and the software is being madeavailable to other OEMS, with Microsoft offering a program for compliancetesting of the completed adaptations.andM;The LAN Manager mutliprocessing model is asymmetrical, allocating oneprocessor to deliver network file service while using the other to augmentperformance for server applications.andM;LAN Manager is also open to other hardware vendors wanting to implementmultiprocessing functionality.andP;  Microsoft is providing the adaptation kitjointly developed with Compaq to other OEMs for implementation in a standardway.andP;  The kit contains source code, documentation, test specifications, andtest software.andP;  Once an OEM has successfully adapted the product to itshadware, Microsoft will perform compliance testing on the OEM'smultiprocessor adaptation.andM;Pricing is based on the number of users rathern than on the number offeatures.andP;  The full-featured version of single-processor LAN Manager has asuggested retail price of $995.andP;  It comes with support for five yearsbuilt-in at no charge.andP;  Each additional set of 10 users had a suggested priceof $995 eachandgt; the price for an unlimited number of users is $5,495.andP;  TheMultiprocessor Serve Pak, at $2,495, may be added to a LAN Manager network ofany size.andM;The LAN Manager Multiprocessor Server Pak comes with its own installationprogram.andP;  Once installed, the Multi-processor Server Pak tells LAN Managerthat another microprocessor is present and starts dividing tasks between thetwo.andM;Information: Brenda Hansen or Marty Taucher, Microsoft Corporation, OneMicrosoft Way, Redmond, WA 98052-6399andgt; (206) 882-8080.andO;</TEXT></DOC>